Act as an expert frontend web developer and conversion copywriter specializing in local service businesses. I am building a reusable website template to pitch to independent local auto repair shops. My agency is called "Morningstar Web Solutions," and my main selling point is that I build fast, mobile-optimized sites that convert visitors into phone calls and scheduled repair jobs.

Please write the complete, production-ready HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript for this demo website.

Technical & Design Requirements:
Tech Stack: Pure HTML5, CSS3, and vanilla JavaScript (no React, no heavy frameworks). It must be fast, lightweight, and easy to host on Netlify.

Design/Aesthetic: Clean, modern, and trustworthy. Use a color palette featuring clean dark tones with gold accents (to match my logo), white backgrounds for main content areas, dark text for high readability, and gold for primary call-to-action buttons.

UX/UI Focus: Mobile-first approach. Use big, easily tappable buttons, clear phone numbers at the top, and no excessive or distracting animations. The focus is strictly on driving Calls, Directions, and Trust.

Website Structure & Content Guidelines:
Please generate the code for the following pages (or a comprehensive single-page structure that simulates them):

1. Home Page (Conversion-focused)

Hero Section: * Headline: "Need Reliable Auto Repair in [City]? Fast. Honest. Certified Technicians."

Primary Button: "Call Now"

Services Overview: Brief grid highlighting core services.

Why Choose Us: Focus on trust, certifications, and speed.

Reviews Preview: Highlight a star rating and a couple of testimonials.

Call to Action: Final push to call or book.

Footer: Map embed placeholder, contact info, and hours.

2. Services Page

List specific, high-intent services: Brake Repair, Oil Changes, Engine Diagnostics, AC Repair, and Transmission Service. * Include a short description, the benefits of choosing this shop, and a "Call to Book" button for each service.

3. About Page (Trust Builder)

Focus on elements that mechanics and their customers care about: Years in business, ASE Certifications, family-owned history, and honest pricing guarantees.

4. Reviews Page

Include a bold header: "Rated 4.9 Stars by 200+ Drivers"

Design a clean layout for 3 to 6 placeholder reviews.

5. Contact Page

Make the phone number huge.

Include an embedded map placeholder, business hours, and a simple, mobile-friendly contact form.

Please provide the index.html (with the homepage structure), a single style.css file that styles all elements beautifully according to the dark/gold theme, and script.js for basic functionality (like a mobile hamburger menu and simple form validation). Ensure the HTML includes placeholder links for the other pages.